data.description: WELCOME TO THE TOWNHOMES AT CAPE HAZE!   This 2 bedroom, 2 bath, OVERSIZED 2 CAR GARAGE townhome is a unique product in a great location.  You are minutes away from shopping, golfing and a short drive to the beautiful beaches in Boca Grande and Englewood.  The lower floor of the unit includes the huge garage (28x32), a spacious entry hall, under stair storage, a back deck for grilling and is even set up for future elevator installation to the second floor.  Up the stairs you will walk into the Great Room which seamlessly combines the living, dining and kitchen areas.  The views of the preserve in the back are fantastic and will provide tranquil enjoyment to any owner.    The Kitchen has had a major makeover including beautiful quartz counter tops, gleaming white cabinets, subway tile backsplash, a farm sink and newer appliances including an attractive stainless steel drop in range.  Both bedrooms are nicely sized and there is a convenient laundry closet located by the guest bath and bedroom with a stacked machine.  Select furnishings are available by separate contract should a buyer be interested.  All special assessments related to Hurricane Ian have been paid by the current owner and the community is coming back together nicely.  FYI ... the yellow siding will be switched out to blue in the restoration plans.  Units like this are rarely available and are very popular because of their uniqueness.  Make you appointment to see this great home today ... You won't be disappointed!
